53.6	Collatz_conjecture	Collatz conjecture	The Collatz conjecture is a conjecture in mathematics named after Lothar Collatz, who first proposed it in 1937. The conjecture is also known as the 3n + 1 conjecture, the Ulam conjecture (after Stanis≈Çaw Ulam), Kakutani's problem (after Shizuo Kakutani), the Thwaites conjecture (after Sir Bryan Thwaites), Hasse's algorithm (after Helmut Hasse), or the Syracuse problem; the sequence of numbers involved is referred to as the hailstone sequence or hailstone numbers, or as wondrous numbers.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ad/Collatz-graph-all-30-no27.svg/100px-Collatz-graph-all-30-no27.svg.png
